So, for one product, we will have 1,000 income from sales.

27:34.000 --> 27:41.000
For 510 products, we will have 510,000 income.

27:41.000 --> 27:44.000
Minus the variable costs,

27:44.000 --> 27:50.000
that is, 500 variable costs.

27:50.000 --> 27:59.000
500 multiplied by 510 will be equal to 255,000 rubles.

27:59.000 --> 28:02.000
Let's recall what 510,000 rubles is.

28:02.000 --> 28:06.000
We had 600,000 rubles.

28:06.000 --> 28:10.000
But as we have just decided,

28:10.000 --> 28:15.000
if we decrease the price by 15%

28:15.000 --> 28:18.000
since we increased the price by 100 rubles,

28:18.000 --> 28:24.000
that is, the price has become 1,000 rubles per product from 900 rubles,

28:24.000 --> 28:30.000
then we should have 600 minus 15%

28:30.000 --> 28:33.000
and it will be 510,000 rubles.

28:33.000 --> 28:41.000
So, the marginal profit will be 1,000 per product minus 500 variable costs.

28:41.000 --> 28:43.000
500 rubles in variable costs.

28:43.000 --> 28:46.000
What do we get? 500 rubles.

